-- Portuguese banks sell 2.8 bln euros of government debt in Sept -ECB
-- By Eva Taylor
-- Mon Oct 27, 2014 05:24AM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, Oct 27 (Reuters) - Portuguese banks in September showed the strongest monthly decline in government debt holdings since December 2013, data from the European Central Bank showed on Monday.

Portuguese banks sold 2.785 billion euros in government debt in September after selling 1.569 billion euros in August, marking the largest decline since December last year. Italian banks also sold 2.073 billion euro in government debt in September after a 1.845 billion euro increase in August.